<br>
Because we're craving an immersive interactive environment (and actually had received it for a while) and now we're getting a treadmill.  All we've been presented with is kill mob X for loot X.  The lore is always incomplete at best and without the lore there's nothing but pixels.  As far as features go I've been very impressed with some of the events that you have created, but why should I bother to do it?  Phat Loot?  That's cool but that gets old very fast.<br>
<br>
I guess what I'm saying is that the elements of plot and fantasy are at best poor.  New challenges as far as mob difficulty is only one part of making a game and seems to be all you (the developers) are concerned with.  How can you even conceive of a fantasy/role play genre with such incomplete plotlines?  The city of Qeynos is incredibly cool with plot lines, all sorts of lore you can learn just by doing random quests throughout that city culminating with the Qeynos badge of Nobility.  Now let's compare LoY?  nuthin.  No immersion, just more stuff to kill.  <br>
<br>
Everquest has the potential to be incredibly fun, but the only reason I log on anymore is to hang with friends I've made from back when I was thrilled to learn of Kane Bayle's corruption, I'm looking for more of that magic.<br>
<br>
