<br>
I think a lot of people here are confusing EverQuest being on any sort of back burner with their own satisfaction of the game.  To me, it's not a question of Sony doing <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>nothing</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> but that they are perhaps doing the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>wrong things</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to keep people happy.<br>
<br>
Flipping through these pages I see people asking for improved CS (ie more GMs), finishing existing content, changing time sinks and several other odds and ends that would help renew the faith of various posters here.  This isn't necessarily that Sony stopped doing these things but that they don't see the importance in them (from either a financial or design standpoint).<br>
<br>
I think the problem nowadays is that after four years Sony has to do a lot more to keep the player base happy.  However, they aren't able to keep up anymore.  People want variety, but there isn't much at the high end game.  PoP exp zones are as boring and tedious as playing in Lake of Ill Omen and provide little challange.  While raids can be dynamic and fun, having to fight over what you can do (on a crowded server) makes the raiding experience more frustrating and blood boiling than fun.  Of course, I suppose this is why CS has been brought up here several times.  It's no more fun to petition and wait hours for a response from a GM than it is to call a computer tech person and be put on hold for a long time.<br>
<br>
The bottom line is they need to be working harder towards making the game more fun and challanging and less on trying to keep people playing with tedious timesinks.  Lose the perception that Sony is just trying to milk EQ for $$$ to the last drop and finish things like EQIM and PoWar.  Go back and redo unused content more often.  As the adage goes, if at first you don't succeed, try and try again.  Where is the everchanging world we were advertised?  GM events and lore in the game are abysmal.  If I wanted to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>read</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a storyline I'd pick up a book.  If I play a game, I'd expect to be able to <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">experience</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> that storyline.  I don't expect to be able to see everything that goes on in the world of Norrath, but I should be able to run into some dynamic content every so often instead of just having Trolls just magically appear in Neriak after one patch like the world of Norrath is constantly jumping ahead in time with no care for the details.<br>
<br>
There is a lot they could do to make the game more enjoyable, fun and challanging.  I just hope when they try to prove that this game isn't on a proverbial backburner that they keep these things in mind.  The game, like a TV show, needs to evolve and change in order to keep us interested. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.aol.com/nodnarbjh/csig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
