<br>
Oh, there are new zones, but exploring them isn't a challange or rewarding. When you are able to move through them with a chance to survive, you won't get xp, and when you can get xp, you need so much back up, a single group ain't enough.<br>
<br>
Story lines are incomplete, quests are incomplete, zones are incomplete.<br>
<br>
Customer Service is non-exsistant. The hard work is done by Guides that have their powers limited to nothing, The GM's hardly show up at all, or take weeks to respond while any evidence has decayed by that time. This causes people to simply give up when that happens, and their friends along with them.<br>
<br>
The promised small/single group content never made it into the Planes of Power, because that content is limited to the annoying XP grind. <br>
<br>
There are no single person quests that are both challanging as rewarding anymore. You either need to spent hours to get some ultra rare item from a rare spawn, or you need to compete with 59 other people on a drop from a mob that needed 60 people and spawns once a week. With challanging, I do NOT mean time consuming. The Staff of the Wheel is a challanging quest, but it aint time consuming.<br>
<br>
Why is it that all the gifted designers, of both quests (ring, shawl, QBadge) and Zones (ToFS (unfinished still) Crystal Caverns (never finished, but changed)) were fired? didn't they give in to the management that wanted to feed the masses with Raw potatoes, while they wanted to finish their product before releasing it?<br>
<br>
What is the link between that Vampire girl in ToFS and the spirit stones from the cats/Kerrans in Stonebrunt?<br>
<br>
Why can't I still comlete the armor, and are the weapons no rent, and is this only an option for those with good faction, and is it impossible to change that faction, why is alot of major content removed from faction groups, without an alternate story line behind them (Katta)<br>
<br>
Who are those Dark elves in Rathe mountains, why don't they talk to a fellow dark elf, and why can't I up my faction with them? <br>
<br>
There are so many questions unanswered, and all we do is run into a wall of missing links and incomplete content.<br>
<br>
After PoP, there was a poll from EQ/SOE about what the customer wanted, about 85% voted for the Fixing of old content and Issues, what happened, another Incomplete expansion was released.<br>
<br>
There have been talks about class balance for several years now. I remember the huge posts about Wizards on the EQ formum when those were still open to everyone. Nothing ever came out of that. Patches were made for every class, but they skipped the wizards. The same with the previous class balance, and now you start over again with pure melee, skipping the Wizard class. All wizards want is some group friendly spells, several good ideas were brought up, none were implemented. In the mean time, wizards get shafted with small changes every time. Some we don't even know until we see some dagger that proc's one of our nukes, or other such things.<br>
<br>
But we are not talking about the wizard class here, we are talking about the Burn out. Well, we get the feeling that EQ is nothing more then a milkcow ready for slaughter. it has been over a year since there was a new issue of the newspaper in game. Content unfinished, Bugs unfixed (until they are used as you did not imagine, like the Eye of Zomm aggro)<br>
<br>
what to do to fix it.<br>
<br>
- Remove the time sinks<br>
<br>
High end Guilds have passed the key time sinks for VP, ST, VT, AC. now instead of 2 guilds, 12 guilds are competing against the same mobs for the same content, result is that it never opens up for those. Solution: increase spawn time from those mobs from once every week to every 20 hours. And make the keyparts common and multiple drops. <br>
<br>
- Fix content<br>
<br>
When does ToFS gets finished?, and PoMischief,  ...<br>
<br>
- Fix mobs, encounters<br>
<br>
Remove those annoying summon ability.<br>
If we can not summon an animal that is 14 levels below us, then that animal should not be able to summon us. Permarooted mobs (like Trees, and lotus flowers) may summon, but everything that can walk, run or fly should not be able to unless we are too. Every time we outsmart a stupid animal in the game, the developers (those that are left behind) feel insulted and give it summoning powers or make it immune to everything. The will o wisp was a nice mob in the beginning before Kunark. This mob could not be hit unless you had a magical weapon, and those were rare. Where are the mobs now, that are pure casters, and can not be hit with melee? nowhere, it is always the other way around, they only give it more HP, make it hit harder or faster and give it an annoying AE and Immune to spells. The mobs that summon companions or proc FD are nice though, make the fight more random and interesting, instead of gathering enough CH clerics and a few heavy hp tanks that hit attack and go to the movies to come back in 3 hours to see that the mob is almost dead. Fixes are made with a blunt object, instead of a scalpel.<br>
<br>
- stop catering to the top end. <br>
<br>
I know that everyone ends up there, but there can be so much fun for those of lower level if only the means was given that they would feel safe in case something goes wrong (Graveyards, close by portals). Mana dependant classes do not like to crawl to much, because they need their mana, but everyone likes to crawl through a dungeon if they know that they can get their corpse out. Risk vs reward can be solved in other ways, like crawling toward a quest mob that gives xp for turned in items you collect on the way. This prevents people camping the mobs for the xp, because half of it they only get on turn in, this also gives people reason to move along. Place a boss type mob along the way in a side room you can skip if you do not want to do him, and make him a challenge for a single group that gives a nice item. some flags and triggers to make the room one group only, and you can crawl. Alot of these things were implemented for PoP, but not for the 25 - 45 group that has nothing better to do then Grind in boring same zones.<br>
<br>
- fix quests<br>
<br>
See all other posts on all other EQ related sites.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
