<br>
Are you telling us that this is supposed to be considered a game anymore when there are ridiculous encounters like the Rathe which REQUIRES you to spend 2+ hours non-stop mezzing and healing without so much as a 30 second break since it would wipe the raid, and requires you to have 70+ people? And that's on a good day. What about 4 1/2 hours of non-stop mezzing and having all those 4 hours of work (fun? HAH) all get erased in 10 seconds simply because the wrong person got shadowstepped at the wrong time? Is that supposed to be fun and? Have devs become so blinded by the almighty dollar that they have forgotten what Everquest is about and that it's supposed to be a goddamn game? <br>
<br>
It seems more and more like SOE is more interested in cockblocking their unfinished expansions lately to stretch them out artificially as much as they can instead of actually bringing out finished content which would keep the masses busy actually progressing through smoothly. Velious was only fully beaten right before Luclin came out, and there was no absolutly retarded timesink to go through (you had to farm gear to progress but that is nowhere near as tedious as farming VT shards off greens or key pieces in Ssra).<br>
<br>
Tech support doesn't even have a 1-800 line anymore. Roving GM's instead of server GM's is somehow supposed to improve customer service? Where are the serverwide events? The Best of the best? Test of Tactics? Did all of these go with the departure of Lady Dae and no replacement was hired? Heck where are ANY events? Take a look at the events message boards on EQlive.com.<br>
<br>
