<br>
There are just so many broken promises and what feels like half-assed broken concepts which keep pouring in that it makes you wonder if anyone at SOE even plays the game. Or better worded, LOVE the game. The original EQ team loved the game. As much as people didn't like some of Brad's ideas about The Vision (what happened to The Vision anyways?), he loved the game and it showed. Kunark was an amazing expansion which while it had lots of class balancing issues, the content itself was true to the game's core places like Sebilis and Howling Stones. DUNGEONS! Where did they all disappear to? The last great dungeon was Dragon Necropolis. The dungeons in Luclin had no heart and were mindnumbingly boring, and Planes of Power had no dungeon at all (Crypt of Decay is the closest thing to one and it's hardly a crawling dungeon)!<br>
<br>
PoP showed a lot of promise, but in the end content was artificially cockblocked yet again to keep players away from unfinished content like it was in Luclin, and the end result is lots of frustration and no fun. Luclin brought the gun. PoP pulled the trigger.<br>
